[1] Cholera - Uganda (Mbarara)
Date: Mon, 14 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org
Source: AllAfrica.com and New Vision (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200406140596.html>

Cholera Hits Mbarara
--------------------
The directorate of health in Mbarara district temporarily closed
open-roofed eating places and suspended the sale of cold drinks in Ibanda,
following an outbreak of cholera.
The district director of health services, Dr. Kaguna Amooti, on Wed, 9 Jun
2004, said at least 3 people, including a medical assistant of Kayemba
clinic in Ishongororo, had succumbed to the disease.
He said 19 other cholera-related cases had been registered in Ishongororo
and Ibanda sub-county dispensaries. Kaguna said 2 of the cases were from
Nganiko village in Nyabani sub-county in Kamwenge district.
Local authorities in Ibanda said the most involved villages were in
Bisheshe and Ishongororo sub-counties.
[Byline: Kyomuhendo Muhanga]
