[2] Cholera - Uganda (Rukungiri)
Date: Tue, 15 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and New Vision (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200406150083.html>

Cholera Kills 2 in Rukungiri
-----------------------------
A suspected cholera outbreak has been reported in Rubumba village, Kebisoni
sub-county in Rukungiri district, where it left 2 people dead. The
district director of health services, Dr. Zepher Karyabakabo, confirmed
reports of the outbreak.
"We have received reports that 2 people in Kebisoni died and we are trying
to find out the truth before we declare that it is cholera," he said.
The dead were aged 5 and 9. The father of the children was hospitalized.
[Byline: Caleb Bahikaho]
--
