[4] Cholera - India (New Delhi)
Date: Tue, 15 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Times of India [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/739505.cms>

Cholera cases continued to be reported from across the city on Mon, 14 Jun
2004 with 10 fresh patients reporting to the Municipal Corporation (MCD) of
Delhi 's Infectious Diseases Hospital. This takes the total number of
cholera cases reported in the city to 825.
Once again, the highest number of cases were reported from the central
zone. Central and civil lines zone have consistently reported highest
number of cholera cases, giving rise to the belief that the drinking water
in this area was contaminated. Joint teams of the MCD and Delhi Jal Board
were also formed to gather water samples from these areas.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
