[5] Salmonellosis - China (Guangdong)
Date: Fri, 18 Jun 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Xinhuanet News, China [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-06/18/content_1534381.htm>

Salmonella [contamination] blamed for mass food poisoning
--------------------------------------------------
Health supervision officials said Fri, 18 Jun 2004, that salmonella
[contamination] was to blame for the mass food poisoning that began on Mon,
14 Jun 2004 in south China's Guangdong Province. The latest number of
victims rose to at least 120 5 days after the accident.
At least 120 customers of 100 Point Artistic Bakery in Meizhou, a city in
Guangdong province, complained of stomach ache, nausea, vomiting, fever and
dehydration and sought medical treatment beginning after eating sandwich
cakes from the bakery chain, the city's health bureau said.
Workers failed to clean and disinfect the eggshells when making the cakes,
according to an investigation by local health supervision authorities. The
salmonella then [contaminated] the one of the [ingredients] of the cakes.
The bakery was ordered to suspend the sale and production of the food
suspected of contamination, and local health authorities have organized a
recall.
