[6] Dysentery - Russia (Moscow)
Date: Thu, 17 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regions.ru [translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.regions.ru/newsheadlines/news/date/20040617.html?section=news&top>
&topic=health>

Dysentery outbreak traced to fast food in Moscow region
-------------------------------------------------
148 people have been identified with signs of an intestinal
infection. These people were personnel of supermarket chain "Ashan" in
Odinzovskiy, Leninskiy, Krasnogorskiy and Mitishinskiy parts of the Moscow
region.
40 of them were discovered with bacterial dysentery due to _Shigella
sonnei_. 16 people were hospitalized. Epidemiological surveillance center
identified that the outbreak is associated with food supplied for the
supermarket.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
