[8] Dysentery, factory - Russia (Moscow)
Date: Sat, 19 Jun 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Itar-Tass 17 Jun 2004 [edited]
<http://www.prime-tass.com/news/show.asp?topicid=0&id=352301>

Russia's Nestle-Zhukovsky plant closes due to dysentery outbreak
-------------------
The Nestle-Zhukovsky confectionery plant of the Russia-based subsidiary of
Switzerland's Nestle Group in the Moscow Region was closed due to an
outbreak of dysentery among 24 employees in early June 2004, an official
with the Federal Service on Consumers' Rights told ITAR-TASS Thursday.
The official said that the operations of the plant had been temporarily
halted and would be resumed only after permission had been granted by an
official from the local Sanitation Service.
The management of the company is now investigating the outbreak of
dysentery among the plant's workers, the company's Director of external
relations, Jennifer Galencamp, told Prime-Tass Thu, 17 Jun 2004.
The source of the infection has not yet been found, she said.
--
